⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Terry McKeen
node LMM · LMM · ⟦Terry McKeen:LMM:d48dc4⟧

WHO   — Terry McKeen — the ordinary world
WHAT  — The plain world the film starts in: the lawns, the pumps, the small life Jobe is taken out of.
WHERE — LMM · The Lawnmower Man (1992)  Framework inputs: The Lawnmower Man (1992, dir. Brett Leonard, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the fear lands harder when it erupts out of an utterly ordinary place.
HOW   — By employing Jobe and standing for the mundane world the experiment overruns.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  He pumped gas and cut grass and never bothered a soul. Whatever they turned him into, it didn't start here.

